## Description

The Claude Code parser skips user messages that contain only images (no text content). These are valid prompts (e.g., screenshots shared with the assistant) but are not being captured.

## Evidence

From verification of `/Users/kulesh/.claude/projects/-Users-kulesh-dev-catsyphon/f953d50d-e348-4b25-a506-746d769c24d6.jsonl`:

- Expected prompts: 203 (164 text + 19 image+text + 12 image-only + 7 multi-image+text + 1 triple-image+text)
- Parsed prompts: 191
- Missing: 12 image-only messages

Sample skipped messages:
```json
{"ts":"2025-11-22T05:19:44.814Z","content_types":["image"]}
{"ts":"2025-11-22T05:25:46.935Z","content_types":["image"]}
```

## Root Cause

In `aiobscura-core/src/ingest/parsers/claude.rs:650-660`, the parser requires non-empty text:

```rust
if !text.is_empty() {
    *seq += 1;
    messages.push(Message {
        // ...
        message_type: MessageType::Prompt,
        content: Some(text.clone()),
        // ...
    });
}
```

Image-only messages have empty text, so they are skipped.

## Proposed Fix

Create a Prompt message for image-only content blocks with:
- `content: None` or `content: Some("[image]")`
- `metadata: { "has_image": true, "image_count": N }`

This preserves the conversation flow and allows analytics to track image usage.
